See what others are saying

[](https://www.linkedin.com/advice/0/youre-analyzing-mergers-impact-companys-debt-rcvff#debt-assumption)1 Debt Assumption
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

When two companies merge, the resulting entity may assume the liabilities of both. This can lead to an increased debt burden, which might negatively impact the credit rating if the post-merger earnings do not sufficiently cover the larger debt service requirements. Credit rating agencies look at metrics such as debt-to-EBITDA (Earnings Before Interest, Taxes, Depreciation, and Amortization) to assess whether a company can sustain its debt. If this ratio worsens significantly post-merger, agencies might downgrade the credit rating, leading to higher borrowing costs.

  

