[](https://www.linkedin.com/advice/0/youre-analyzing-mergers-impact-companys-debt-rcvff#synergies-effect)2 Synergies Effect
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Mergers often aim for synergies—cost savings or revenue enhancements that occur when two companies combine operations. If these synergies are realized, they can improve cash flows and the ability to service debt, potentially leading to a better credit rating. However, if the anticipated synergies are not achieved, or the costs to realize them are higher than expected, the merger can have a negative impact on the credit rating. The uncertainty of achieving these synergies is a factor credit agencies may consider when evaluating the merger's impact.

  

[Add your perspective](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=%2Fadvice%2F0%2Fyoure-analyzing-mergers-impact-companys-debt-rcvff&trk=article-ssr-frontend-x-article)

           

