[](https://www.linkedin.com/advice/0/youre-analyzing-mergers-impact-companys-debt-rcvff#debt-restructuring)3 Debt Restructuring
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Post-merger, companies may restructure their debt, which can involve refinancing old debt at different interest rates or terms, or issuing new debt to pay off existing obligations. This can affect the credit rating depending on how the restructuring is perceived. If it leads to more favorable terms and lower interest expenses, it could be positive for the credit rating. Conversely, if restructuring results in higher costs or reflects financial distress, it could lead to a downgrade.

  

[Add your perspective](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=%2Fadvice%2F0%2Fyoure-analyzing-mergers-impact-companys-debt-rcvff&trk=article-ssr-frontend-x-article)

           

